WEBVTT

00:02.021 --> 00:03.310
Previously on "Nashville"...

00:03.336 --> 00:05.733
You're still digging out
from the hit you took

00:05.734 --> 00:07.134
when Teddy's development went bust.

00:07.135 --> 00:10.174
Bottom line, Joe. Stop spending money.

00:10.175 --> 00:13.133
You think he's lying about something.

00:13.134 --> 00:15.713
A mayor with secrets is easier to control.

00:15.714 --> 00:18.053
What is his problem with my career?

00:18.054 --> 00:20.967
He hates your career because of mom.

00:20.968 --> 00:25.217
Mom had a singer/songwriter friend.
You mean like an affair?

00:25.218 --> 00:27.341
You've proven to have the same disregard

00:27.342 --> 00:30.091
for your marriage that she did for ours.

00:30.092 --> 00:31.412
I'm trying to do the right thing,

00:31.413 --> 00:33.051
but none of it feels right to me.

00:33.052 --> 00:35.431
I feel like I need to be letting you go.

00:35.432 --> 00:37.011
So why don't you, Ray?

00:37.012 --> 00:39.671
My mother is a drug addict.

00:39.672 --> 00:43.171
I need you. There was a time
when I needed you, too.

00:43.172 --> 00:46.051
I'm your mama!

00:46.052 --> 00:47.511
Your girlfriend's got it.

00:47.512 --> 00:50.131
I think she feels like you
might, you know, leave her.

00:50.132 --> 00:52.532
What is going on with getting
Deacon Claybourne on my tour?

00:52.533 --> 00:53.171
I want him.

00:53.172 --> 00:54.652
You deserve someone you can count on.

00:54.653 --> 00:57.261
I'm not that guy.

00:57.262 --> 00:59.011
Look.

00:59.012 --> 01:01.172
It's Juliette Barnes.

